REFUGE-P License (Phase 0 / Phase 1)
1. Scope of License

This repository documents the REFUGE-P (Hard Stop) system at Phase 0 and Phase 1 only. The contents are provided for review, evaluation, study, and internal discussion.

This license governs all text, diagrams, figures, concepts, architectures, and system definitions contained in this repository.

2. Permitted Uses (Free)

The following uses are permitted without fee:

Reading, reviewing, and evaluating the material

Internal discussion, critique, and analysis

Educational or academic reference

Non-commercial concept comparison

Internal feasibility assessment by government agencies or contractors

No permission is granted beyond these uses.

3. Prohibited Uses Without a Commercial License

The following actions are explicitly prohibited without a separate, paid license agreement:

Physical construction or fabrication of any REFUGE-P-derived system

Prototype development beyond internal thought experiments

Incorporation into proposals, bids, or funded programs

Inclusion in commercial products, services, or offerings

Derivative works intended for execution, testing, or deployment

Submission of this material as part of SBIRs, NIACs, or similar funding vehicles

Reading is free. Execution is not.

4. Commercial / Execution License Requirement

Any intent to build, test, prototype, integrate, or deploy a system derived from this repository requires a separate commercial execution license prior to execution.

Licensing terms are negotiated separately and may include:

One-time license fees

Program-specific rights

Attribution and disclosure terms

No rights are implied by silence or omission.

